.TH GAT-DOCTOR 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-doctor \- inspect local setup, dependencies, and stale worktrees
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat doctor
.RB [ \-\-format
.IR text|json ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reports the Git version, repository roots, ticket prefix, whether shell
integration is active, and the availability of
.BR docker (1),
.BR tmux (1),
.IR codex ,
.BR nvim (1),
and
.BR fzf (1).
It also warns about worktrees not accessed in over 30 days and prunes orphaned
metadata entries as a side effect.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat doctor
gat doctor \-\-json
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-prune (1),
.BR gat\-shell\-init (1)
